CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 7, 1953, pg. 3, reads: "On Election Day ...In the right photo, a group of Democrats and Republicans was snapped at Madison School polling place for the eighth district of the Fifth Ward, during a slowdown of voters Tuesday afternoon. Left to right, they are Thomas Robinson, Alice Watson, Joseph Moss, Alfred Wilson, Cecil Slater, Curtis Haines and John Mills. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Thomas Robinson holding notepad, Alice Watson, Joseph Moss, Alfred Wilson, Cecil Slater, Curtis Haines holding cigar, and John Mills standing outside of Madison Elementary School, polling place for eighth district, Fifth Ward, on 1953 election day
